    <text>
        <body>
            <head>165. Notes of a Conversation<note n="1" place="foot" type="source"
                    xml:id="d165fn1">Source: <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">Reagan</persName>
                    Library, <persName corresp="recUYtGB7FjTqe0WT">Charles Hill</persName> Papers,
                        <persName corresp="recUYtGB7FjTqe0WT">Charles Hill</persName> Notebooks,
                    entry for October 12, 1986. No classification marking. Drafted by <persName
                        corresp="recUYtGB7FjTqe0WT">Hill</persName>. The editor transcribed the
                    portion of the text here specifically for this volume. An image of the notes is
                    Appendix <persName corresp="recXTrNyt2vU9QpAl">G</persName>.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Reykjavik</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1986-10-12"
                        >October 12, 1986</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>1555/<persName corresp="recUYtGB7FjTqe0WT">CH</persName> as notetaker/ <persName
                    corresp="recXTrNyt2vU9QpAl">G</persName> + <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq"
                    >P</persName> banter + argue as <persName corresp="reczYQHQnMCD2hSLc"
                    >Shev</persName> ponders + <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">S</persName>
                drafts to try to find a formula</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">P</persName>—were so close. may I suggest</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="recXTrNyt2vU9QpAl">G</persName>—a pt of substance. Mr. <persName
                    corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">P</persName> draw yr attn.—our prop has such a wdg.
                after 10 yr pd the sides in negos wd find further must accept solutions in This
                field, That is, the <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss>. Our prop allows us to take
                acct. of all positions as they [illegible] enough after 10 years. You, <gloss
                    target="#t_SDI_1">
                    <rs type="program" corresp="recVUMTljdyxyuZz3">SDI</rs>
                </gloss>: we don’t agree. We put something + y don’t agree.</p>
            <p>- to sum up. 10 yr pd w two sides not <rs type="compound-subject"
                    corresp="recXrGW53dEgm0PM4">w/d</rs> [illegible]. Can conduct <hi
                    rendition="simple_italic">lab</hi>
                <rs type="topic" corresp="recJclekZAp3yKmD5">research</rs>. After 10, during 10, we
                complete elim all stratg wpons.</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">P</persName>—If both elim. nucl wpons, why a
                concern if one side wants to build def syst just in case? Are y considering starting
                up ag After 10 yrs again w wpns? I have a diff picture. I have a pic after 10 yrs,
                yo + I come to Iceland each bring the last 2 missiles in the world + we have the
                biggest damn party in celebration.</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="recXTrNyt2vU9QpAl">G</persName>—Mr. <persName
                    corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">P</persName> we close to mut. accep formula Don’t
                think we have evil designs, we don’t.</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">P</persName>—a mtg in Iceland in 10 yrs. Ill
                be so old y wont recog me. I’ll say M. you’ll say Ron? + we’ll destroy the 2.</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="recXTrNyt2vU9QpAl">G</persName>—I may not be lvg after these
                10</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">P</persName>—I’ll count on it.</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="recXTrNyt2vU9QpAl">G</persName>—Now y can go smoothly to 100, you
                passed the tough period. I’m just entering it. Beyond that, I’ll have burden of
                having gone thru all these mtg w <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">P</persName>
                who doesn’t like concessions, He wants to be a winner. We must both be winners.</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">P</persName>—I can’t live to 100 worrying
                you’ll shoot one of those m. at me.</p>
            <pb facs="0764" n="737" xml:id="pg_737"/>
            <p>- 50%—we both got it. You told yr people 10 yrs + y got it. I told my people I wdnt
                give up <gloss target="#t_SDI_1">
                    <rs type="program" corresp="recVUMTljdyxyuZz3">SDI</rs>
                </gloss>. So I have to go home showing I haven’t. Our people will cheer that we got
                rid of the missiles.</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="recXTrNyt2vU9QpAl">G</persName>. well, what can say about r + t
                in lab constitutes basis + opp for y to go on w/I [illegible] of <gloss
                    target="#t_SDI_1">
                    <rs type="program" corresp="recVUMTljdyxyuZz3">SDI</rs>
                </gloss>. So y have not renounced <gloss target="#t_SDI_1">
                    <rs type="program" corresp="recVUMTljdyxyuZz3">SDI</rs>
                </gloss> on yr side</p>
            <p>—I am conv. oppo of sit where is a winner + loser in our mtg. If that case, then
                after agrt + ratify, the loser wd take steps to undermine the agrmt. So that cant be
                basis. Has to be eq. footing. Otherwise you can say agrmt in keeping of US + I cant
                say its in int of <gloss target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss> So docs shd be deserving of
                ratif if in int of both sides.</p>
            <p>
                <persName corresp="rec5PPNCl6qqfgBAq">P</persName>—Whats wrong w going by this +
                then say R, dev of + +g permitted by <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss>—we
                reserved that for our mtg in the <hi rendition="simple_italic">summer</hi> Then <rs
                    type="compound-subject" corresp="recFUg0jqFk2tUZ15">testing</rs>—we then cd disc
                whether it under <gloss target="#t_ABM_1">ABM</gloss> prov.</p>
            <p>
                <hi rendition="simple_italic">TS</hi> returns</p>
        </body>
    </text>
